Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 10:22 AM Defendant Amanda L Daniels not in court.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court.  Prosecuting attorney Alexander Paul Seifert in court for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews file, defendant was in Court when last court date was set. State asks for bench warrant, body or $750.00. Court so orders.

9:11 AM Prosecuting attorney Alexander Paul Seifert in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Amanda L Daniels in court.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court. Court reviews file, asks why she does not have counsel. Defendant responds, tells why she does not have counsel yet, waiting on quarterly payment from her tribe, states she will contact attorneys today and sign contracts, will contact Cveykus. Court gives ramifications of appearing again without counsel, will allow one more adjournment but instructed to get an attorney today, reminds of right to attorney and right to represent herself, can apply to SPD or county appointed as well, continues bond, sets for AIA on 9/7/22 at 9:30 AM.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for September 7, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Adjourned initial appearance on September 7, 2022 at 09:30 am.

9:06 AM Prosecuting attorney Alexander Paul Seifert in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Amanda L Daniels in court. Daniels has received a copy of her complaint. Court reads charges and penalties. Daniels understands. Court questions if she has contacted an attorney. Daniels has but needs time to retain money for an attorney, does not qualify for SPD. Court will allow adjournment to allow time for her to obtain an attorney and continues bond.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for August 10, 2022 at 09:00 am.
